  "text": "Found all client-side retry and timeout policy files in etcd-io/etcd's client/v3 package. The key files are: (1) **retry_interceptor.go** - the gRPC unary and stream retry interceptors with backoff logic, based on grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-middleware/retry; (2) **retry.go** - per-service retry client wrappers (retryKVClient, retryLeaseClient) that annotate RPCs with repeatable/nonRepeatable policy and implement isSafeRetryImmutableRPC/isSafeRetryMutableRPC; (3) **client.go** - client construction wiring interceptors with WithUnaryInterceptor/WithStreamInterceptor, dialWithBalancer for load-balanced connections, waitForConnection for health checking via gRPC health endpoint; (4) **options.go** - default retry limits (100 unary, max uint stream), backoff wait (25ms), jitter (10%), WaitForReady policy; (5) **config.go** - Config struct with DialTimeout, DialKeepAliveTime/Timeout, MaxUnaryRetries, BackoffWaitBetween; (6) **internal/resolver/resolver.go** - EtcdManualResolver implementing round_robin load balancing and endpoint management; (7) **internal/endpoint/endpoint.go** - endpoint URL parsing/translation for the resolver; (8) **kv.go** - KV operations using RetryKVClient with context-based timeout enforcement; (9) **watch.go** - watch stream retry with exponential backoff in openWatchClient/newWatchClient; (10) **lease.go** - lease keepalive with deadlineLoop for TTL-based timeout enforcement and firstKeepAliveTimeout.",
